1450","1427–1499":"1427–1499","1425–Female":"1425–Deceased","1425":"1425","1499":"1499","1400":"1400","About 1425":"about 1425","1450":"1450","1427":"1427","Normanton, Yorkshire, England":"Normanton, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Melton, Yorkshire, England":"Melton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Syward","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Middlesex): variant of   Seward  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Sowards","meanings":["English: variant of   Soward  ."]},{"name":"Seward","meanings":["English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Seward</i> (Old English <i>Sǣweard</i>, from <i>sǣ</i> ‘sea’ + <i>weard</i> ‘guard’).","English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Siward</i>, <i>Seward</i> (Old English <i>Sigeweard</i>, from <i>sige</i> ‘victory’ + <i>weard</i> ‘guard’, or the equivalent Old Norse <i>Sigwarth</i>).","Irish (Cork): shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Suaird</b>, <b>Ó Suairt</b>, usually Anglicized as   Sword  ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Robert Syward was born about 1425, in Melton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Robert Syward."},"et":{"About 1425–":"umbes 1425–Surnud","1400–1450":"1400–1450","1427–1499":"1427–1499","1425–Female":"1425–Surnud","1425":"1425","1499":"1499","1400":"1400","About 1425":"umbes 1425","1450":"1450","1427":"1427","Normanton, Yorkshire, England":"Normanton, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Melton, Yorkshire, England":"Melton, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"About 1425–":"noin 1425–Kuollut","1400–1450":"1400–1450","1427–1499":"1427–1499","1425–Female":"1425–Kuollut","1425":"1425","1499":"1499","1400":"1400","About 1425":"noin 1425","1450":"1450","1427":"1427","Normanton, Yorkshire, England":"Normanton, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Melton, Yorkshire, England":"Melton, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"About 1425–":"environ 1425–Décédée","1400–1450":"1400–1450","1427–1499":"1427–1499","1425–Female":"1425–Décédée","1425":"1425","1499":"1499","1400":"1400","About 1425":"environ 1425","1450":"1450","1427":"1427","Normanton, Yorkshire, England":"Normanton, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Melton, Yorkshire, England":"Melton, Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Robert Syward est née environ 1425, à Melton, Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Robert Syward."},"de":{"About 1425–":"um 1425–Verstorben","1400–1450":"1400–1450","1427–1499":"1427–1499","1425–Female":"1425–Verstorben","1425":"1425","1499":"1499","1400":"1400","About 1425":"um 1425","1450":"1450","1427":"1427","Normanton, Yorkshire, England":"Normanton, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Melton, Yorkshire, England":"Melton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Robert Syward wurde um 1425 in Melton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hatte mit Robert Syward mindesten